Bloody Sunday;;91;;92;;R;;On January 30, 1972, in the Northern Irish town of Derry, a peaceful protest march led by civil rights activist Ivan Cooper (James Nesbitt) turned into a slaughter. British soldiers suddenly opened fire on the defenseless crowd, killing 13 people and wounding 14 more. Shot as if a documentary, this film follows Ivan throughout the day as it chronicles the events leading up to the horrific incident and the bloodied, confused aftermath that followed.;;Drama,History;;Paul Greengrass;;2002;;James Nesbitt,Tim Pigott-Smith,Nicholas Farrell,Gerard McSorley,Kathy Kiera Clarke,Allan Gildea,Gerard Crossan,Mary Moulds,Carmel McCallion,Declan Duddy;;https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/bloody_sunday